  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1982-06-24", 
    "text": "Amends the Federal criminal code to authorize a verdict of \"guilty but mentally ill\" even if such illness would not constitute criminal insanity. Permits the court to impose on a defendant found guilty but mentally ill any sentence which the court can impose on a defendant convicted of such offense. Allows the Attorney General to take any necessary action to assure that a defendent found guilty but mentally ill receives appropriate treatment while serving a sentence of imprisonment or a probationary sentence."
